        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 3:54PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Pickens, or near Lake Jocassee, moving southwest
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Salem, Devils Fork State Park, Gorges State Park, Keowee Toxaway
State Park, Jocassee Gorges, Lake Jocassee, Lake Keowee, Sunset,
Sassafras Mountain, and Nine Times.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
